%% How a closure captures drives which Fn* trait it implements.
flowchart TD
    Q{What does the closure do with captured values?}
    Q -->|only reads them| Fn["Fn — &self, callable many times"]
    Q -->|mutates them| FnMut["FnMut — &mut self, callable many times"]
    Q -->|consumes them| FnOnce["FnOnce — self, callable exactly once"]

    Fn --> Move1["move closure still Fn, but owns its captures"]
    FnMut --> Move2["move closure still FnMut, but owns its captures"]
    FnOnce --> Move3["move closure still FnOnce"]

    note1["move keyword: take ownership of captures. It does NOT change which Fn trait you implement — it changes WHAT you own."]
    Move1 -.-> note1
